Episodes.Title: Rose
Episodes.Plot:
Location: London, England
Date: 4th/5th/6th March 2005
Enemy: Nestene Consciousness

Rose Tyler stumbles across a man called The Doctor as he seeks out the Nestene Consciousness, to prevent the living plastic it is controlling from taking over the world.
Episodes.GuestStars: Camille Coduri, Adam McCoy, Elli Garnett, Mark Benton, Noel Clarke, Nicholas Briggs, Alan Ruscoe, Paul Kasey, David Sant, Elizabeth Fost, Helen Otway, Sarah K Chrispin

Episodes.Title: The End of the World
Episodes.Plot:
Location: Platform 1 (A space station orbiting Earth)
Date: 5,000,000,000 AD
Enemy: The Lady Cassandra

The Doctor takes Rose on her first voyage through time: to the year five billion, when the Sun is about to expand and swallow the Earth. She is cautious and soon starts to question her reasons for joining The Doctor. But amongst the powerful alien races gathering to watch on Platform One, a murderer is at work. Who is controlling the mysterious and deadly metal spiders?
Episodes.GuestStars: Camille Coduri, Silas Carson, Beccy Armory, Sara Stewart, Jimmy Vee, Yasmin Bannerman, ZoÃ« Wanamaker, Simon Day

Episodes.Title: The Unquiet Dead
Episodes.Plot:
Location: Cardiff, Wales
Date: 24th December, 1869
Enemy: The Gelth

The Doctor plans to take Rose back through time to Naples, 1860, but instead they arrive in Cardiff, 1869. In Victorian Cardiff, the dead are walking and creatures made of gas are on the loose. The time-travellers team up with Charles Dickens to investigate Mr Sneed, the local undertaker, who's hiding a very big secret. However, this time, The Doctor won't be able to save everyone.
Episodes.GuestStars: Zoe Thorne, Wayne Cater, Meic Povey, Alan David, Simon Callow, Jennifer Hill, Huw Rhys, Eve Myles

Episodes.Title: Aliens of London (1)
Episodes.Plot:
Location: London, Earth
Date: March, 2006
Enemy: Slitheen

The  Doctor and Rose return to modern-day Earth, only to find it has been a year since Rose first set off, and everyone thought she was missing, presumed dead. Whilst there, a spaceship crashes into Big Ben and lands in the Thames. Soon, all is not as it seems with the residents of 10 Downing Street.
Episodes.GuestStars: Fiesta Mei Ling, Jimmy Vee, Andrew Marr, Basil Chung, Jack Tarlton, Corey Doabe, Paul Kasey, Navin Chowdhry, Ceris Jones, Lachele Carl, Rupert Vansittart, Steve Spiers, Elizabeth Fost, Camille Coduri, David Verrey

Episodes.Title: World War Three (2)
Episodes.Plot:
Location: London, Earth
Date: March, 2006
Enemy: Slitheen

With the Doctor, Rose, and MP Harriet Jones trapped inside Downing Street, the Slitheen make their move: Nuclear Warfare. If the human race is obliterated, the Earth can be sold on the Galactic Black Market for a very reasonable price. It's up to the Doctor to defeat the Slitheen before the entire population of the Earth is wiped out. But will he have to make the ultimate sacrifice: Rose Tyler...?
Episodes.GuestStars: Alan Ruscoe, Paul Kasey, Elizabeth Fost, Noel Clarke, Jack Tarlton, Steve Spiers, Annette Badland, Morgan Hopkins, Rupert Vansittart, Corey Doabe, Lachele Carl, Penelope Wilton, Camille Coduri, David Verrey, Andre

Episodes.Title: Dalek
Episodes.Plot:
Location: Utah, Earth
Date: 2012
Enemy: Dalek

The Doctor and Rose find themselves in an underground museum in Utah in the year 2012. The museum houses all kinds of extra-terrestrial artefacts the only living exhibit being one of the Doctor's oldest enemies - a Dalek. But soon after, it escapes from its "torture chamber," and goes on a killing spree. Will Rose be one of the victims?
Episodes.GuestStars: Nicholas Briggs, Joe Montana, Jana Carpenter, John Schwab, Nigel Whitmey, Bruno Langley, Anna-Louise Plowman, Corey Johnson, Steven Beckingham, Barnaby Edwards

Episodes.Title: The Long Game
Episodes.Plot:
Location: Satellite 5
Date: 200,000
Enemy: The Editor, Jagrafess

The Doctor, Rose and Adam arrive in the year 200,000 on a broadcasting station that transmits programming to Earth. But soon, trouble is afoot, when they discover that any worker promoted to a position on level 500 never returns. The Doctor and Rose attempt to find out what is happening, whilst Adam investigates part of the station himself, and makes a decision that he's going to regret for the rest of his life.
Episodes.ParentalRatingReason: PG Some scenes may scare very young children
Episodes.GuestStars: Simon Pegg, Tamsin Greig, Anna Maxwell-Martin, Christine Adams, Colin Prockter, Bruno Langley

Episodes.Title: Father's Day
Episodes.Plot:
Location: London, Earth
Date: 1986
Enemy: The Reapers

Rose requests a trip back to the day her father, Pete Tyler, died. Reluctantly, the Doctor agrees, but he realises he has made a mistake, when Rose saves Pete from being run over by a car. This has now changed the timeline, and Reapers are transposing themselves all over the Universe. However, this time, the Doctor doesn't have a plan?
Episodes.ParentalRatingReason: PG Some scenes may scare very young children
Episodes.GuestStars: Rhian James, Julia Joyce, Natalie Jones, Frank Rozelaar-Green, Christopher Llewellyn, Casey Dyer, Shaun Dingwall, Camille Coduri, Eirlys Bellin, Robert Barton

Episodes.Title: The Empty Child (1)
Episodes.Plot:
Location: London, England
Date: 1941
Enemy: The Empty Child

After chasing an unexplained capsule through time, the TARDIS lands in London, during an air raid. Rose investigates when a small child wearing a gasmask, standing on a rooftop, continuously calls out for his mummy. After floating above the city on a barrage balloon, Rose is swept off her feet by another time traveller ? Captain Jack Harkness. Meanwhile, The Doctor follows a teenaged girl to a meeting of the homeless children of the Bl

Episodes.GuestStars: Kate Harvey, Albert Valentine, Florence Hoath, Cheryl Fergison, Damian Samuels, Robert Hands, Joseph Tremain, Jordan Murphy, Brandon Miller, Richard Wilson, Noah Johnson, Dian Perry

Episodes.Title: The Doctor Dances (2)
Episodes.Plot:
Location: London, England
Date: 1941
Enemy: The Empty Child, Nanogenes

After narrowly escaping the gas mask monsters, The Doctor, Rose, and Captain Jack try to stop the mutated people from infecting other victims. But it soon becomes apparent that one of the group may indirectly responsible for the virus. The answer lies at the bomb site, but time is running out...
Episodes.ParentalRatingReason: PG Some scenes may scare very young children
Episodes.GuestStars: Albert Valentine, Dian Perry, Florence Hoath, Luke Perry, Damian Samuels, Cheryl Fergison, Joseph Tremain, Richard Wilson, Robert Hands, Jordan Murphy, Noah Johnson, Martin Hodgson, Vilma Hollingbery

Episodes.Title: Boom Town
Episodes.Plot:
Location: Cardiff, Wales
Date: 2006
Enemy: Margaret Blaine (Blon Fel Fotch Pasameer-Day Slitheen)

The Doctor, Rose and Captain Jack stop off in present-day Cardiff to recharge the TARDIS on the Rift they formerly encountered in 1869. Whilst there, they come upon a since-thought-long-dead enemy of theirs, who is hatching yet another plan to destroy Earth.
Episodes.GuestStars: Annette Badland, William Thomas, Noel Clarke, Alan Ruscoe, Mali Harries, Aled Pedick

Episodes.Title: Bad Wolf (1)
Episodes.Plot:
Location: The Gamestation (Satellite 5)
Date: 200,100
Enemy: The Games, The Daleks

In a seemingly futuristic world, the Doctor wakes up in the Big Brother house during an eviction, Rose wakes up on the Weakest Link with the Anne-Droid, and Captain Jack gets a make over with Trin-E and Zu-Zana. But something unusual is happening, and the losing contestants are being disintergrated. Obviously, it's time for the Doctor to investigate. There could be only one monster behind this - the Daleks!
Episodes.GuestStars: Jo Stone-Fewings, Susannah Constantine, Trinny Woodall, Jo Stone Fewings, Jenna Russell, Paterson Joseph, David Hankinson, Alan Ruscoe, Abi Eniola, Dominic Burgess, Jamie Bradley, Jo Joyner, Karren Winchester, Ka

Episodes.Title: The Parting of the Ways (2)
Episodes.Plot:
Location: The Gamestation (Satellite 5)
Date: 200,100
Enemy: Emperor Dalek, The Daleks

The fate of the Universe is hanging in the balance as the Dalek fleet begin their invasion of Earth. The Doctor must decide whether to sacrifice every human being on Earth in order to save every other living creature in the universe from the Daleks. Either way, he knows he must send Rose home...
Episodes.GuestStars: Nicholas Pegg, David Hankinson, Anne Robinson, Nicholas Briggs, Camille Coduri, Jo Stone-Fewings, Noel Clarke, Nisha Nayar, Jo Joyner, Paterson Joseph, David Tennant, Alan Ruscoe, Barnaby Edwards

Episodes.Title: The Christmas Invasion
Episodes.Plot: As the newly regenerated Doctor drifts in and out of consciousness, Christmas becomes a time of terror on planet Earth with the whole of mankind falling under the shadow of the sinister alien Sycorax.
